data.current_description: Checks whether an operation on a service should be allowed to proceed based on the configuration of the service and related policies. It must be called before the operation is executed. If feasible, the client should cache the check results and reuse them for 60 seconds. In case of any server errors, the client should rely on the cached results for much longer time to avoid outage. WARNING: There is general 60s delay for the configuration and policy propagation, therefore callers MUST NOT depend on the `Check` method having the latest policy information. NOTE: the CheckRequest has the size limit (wire-format byte size) of 1MB. This method requires the `servicemanagement.services.check` permission on the specified service. For more information, see [Cloud IAM](https://cloud.google.com/iam).
data.summary_suggestion: Check if service operation is allowed
data.description_suggestion: Checks whether an operation should be allowed to proceed based on service configuration and policies. Must be called before operation execution. Returns CheckResponse indicating permission status and any applicable errors. Clients should cache results for 60 seconds and extend caching during server errors to prevent outages. Note: 60-second propagation delay exists for policy changes, so latest policy information is not guaranteed. Request size limited to 1MB. Requires `servicemanagement.services.check` permission.

data.current_description: Reports operation results to Google Service Control, such as logs and metrics. It should be called after an operation is completed. If feasible, the client should aggregate reporting data for up to 5 seconds to reduce API traffic. Limiting aggregation to 5 seconds is to reduce data loss during client crashes. Clients should carefully choose the aggregation time window to avoid data loss risk more than 0.01% for business and compliance reasons. NOTE: the ReportRequest has the size limit (wire-format byte size) of 1MB. This method requires the `servicemanagement.services.report` permission on the specified service. For more information, see [Google Cloud IAM](https://cloud.google.com/iam).
data.description_suggestion: Reports operation results to Service Control including logs and metrics after operation completion. Accepts ReportRequest with aggregated telemetry data and returns ReportResponse. Clients should aggregate reporting data for up to 5 seconds to reduce API traffic while minimizing data loss risk (target <0.01%) during client crashes. Request size limited to 1MB. Requires `servicemanagement.services.report` permission.
